Package kaitech.api.database

Interface SaleTable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SaleTblImpl
    public interface SaleTable
    The SaleTable interface declares required functionality to store, retrieve, and modify sales in the database.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getSale

        Sale getSale​(int receiptNo)
        Retrieves a sale from the cache. If the sale does not currently exist in the cache, query the database for the sale. If the query is successful, add the sale to the cache and return it.
        Parameters:
        receiptNo - The integer receipt number of the sale to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        A Sale if the sale exists, null if it does not.

      • getAllReceiptNo

        java.util.Set<java.lang.Integer> getAllReceiptNo()
        Get all receipt numbers for sales currently in the database.
        Returns:
        A set of all integer receipt numbers.

      • putSale

        Sale putSale​(Sale from)
        Saves a given sale to the database, and returns a database managed Sale which is responsible for the automatic saving of changes on setter calls.
        Parameters:
        from - The Sale to be saved.
        Returns:
        Database managed Sale responsible for automatic saving on setter calls.

      • removeSale

        void removeSale​(int receiptNo)
        Remove a sale from the database and cache.
        Parameters:
        receiptNo - The receipt number of the sale to be removed.

      • resolveAllSales

        java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,​Sale> resolveAllSales()
        Gets all sale objects from the database. Warning: this can be a costly operation when everything isn't already cached, please use with care.
        Returns:
        A map from receipt number to Sale.
